{{Expand Japanese|豊国神社|date=November 2025}} <!--interwikis from wikidata-->[[en:Toyokuni Shrine]][[fa:معبدهای تویوکونی]][[fr:Toyokuni-jinja]][[ja:豊国神社]][[ko:도요쿠니 신사]][[zh:豐國神社]] {{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q1208955]] Wikidata name: Toyokuni Shrine [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 10:03, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{nihongo|'''Toyokuni Shrine'''|豊国神社 or 豐國神社|Toyokuni-jinja}}, alternately read '''Hōkoku Shrine''' (''Hōkoku-jinja''), refers to a number of Shinto shrines in Japan dedicated to [[:en:Kampaku|Kampaku]] and ruler of Japan Toyotomi Hideyoshi. The two names are different readings of the same ''kanji'' and are used interchangeably for some shrines.
'''Toyokuni Shrine''' or '''Hōkoku Shrine''' may refer to:
*[[:en:Hōkoku Shrine (Osaka)|Hōkoku Shrine (Osaka)]] in Osaka, Osaka Prefecture *[[:en:Toyokuni Shrine (Kanazawa)|Toyokuni Shrine (Kanazawa)]] in Kanazawa, Ishikawa Prefecture *[[:en:Toyokuni Shrine (Nagoya)|Toyokuni Shrine (Nagoya)]] in Nagoya, Aichi Prefecture *[[:en:Toyokuni Shrine (Kyoto)|Toyokuni Shrine (Kyoto)]] in Kyoto, Kyoto Prefecture *Toyokuni Shrine, located on the grounds of [[Itsukushima Shrine]] in Hatsukaichi, Hiroshima Prefecture
