'''Toyokuni Shrine''' (とよくにじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} enshrined in Nakagō-chō, {{ill|lt=Komatsushima|Q823493|WD=Q823493|1=Komatsushima, Tokushima}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|WD=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}.

=== History ===
Founded in {{ill|lt=1614|Q6781|WD=Q6781|1=1614}} ({{ill|lt=Keichō|Q1328185|WD=Q1328185|1=Keichō}} 19). Toyorin-ji Temple was also built as its bettō temple. As the sacred object, it has a “wooden image of Taikō Toyotomi” (not publicly displayed), received from {{ill|lt=Toyotomi Hideyori|Q313641|WD=Q313641|1=Toyotomi Hideyori}} by {{ill|lt=Hachisuka Iemasa|Q1073557|WD=Q1073557|1=Hachisuka Iemasa}} and {{ill|lt=Hachisuka Yoshishige|Q3125481|WD=Q3125481|1=Hachisuka Yoshishige}} after the death of {{ill|lt=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Q187550|WD=Q187550|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi}}.

At the time of foundation it was a grand major shrine, but it was dismantled because {{ill|lt=Hachisuka Mitsutaka|Q3125458|WD=Q3125458|1=Hachisuka Mitsutaka}}, lord of the {{ill|lt=Tokushima Domain|Q3034557|WD=Q3034557|1=Tokushima Domain}}, feared the {{ill|lt=Edo shogunate|Q205662|WD=Q205662|1=Tokugawa shogunate}} and {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Tokugawa family|1=UNKNOWN}}. In the {{ill|lt=Shōhō|Q1146192|WD=Q1146192|1=Shōhō}} era, Toyorin-ji became abandoned. Afterward it was renamed Toyokuni Daimyōjin, Hiyoshi Daimyōjin, and Hiyoshi-no-miya, and from the {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} period it was restored under the name Toyokuni Shrine by surrounding parishioners.

In the precincts stands Mikata Shrine, a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}, also called Miyakata Shrine.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* {{ill|lt=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Q187550|WD=Q187550|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi}}
** The sacred image “wooden Taikō Toyotomi image” is said to be the only surviving one of the one hundred distributed after Hideyoshi’s death.

=== Precinct shrines ===
[[File:Miagata shrine, Komatsushima, Tokushima.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Mikata Shrine]]
* Mikata Shrine - {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}. Alternate name: Miyakata Shrine. Deity is {{ill|Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|WD=Q276944|1=Ōkuninushi}} or {{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|1=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|WD=Q8009611}}.
* Sumiyoshi Shrine
* Yuga Shrine
* Katō Kiyomasa Shrine

=== Access ===
* About 10 minutes on foot from {{ill|lt=Nakata Station (Tokushima)|Q5119016|WD=Q5119016|lt=Nakata Station|1=Chūden Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Mugi Line|Q860478|WD=Q860478|1=Mugi Line}} ({{ill|lt=JR Shikoku|Q496531|WD=Q496531|1=Shikoku Railway Company}}).

